snippet.title: Supergirl | Official Teaser Trailer
snippet.description:
Look out. #Supergirl lands in theaters June 26.

‚ÄúSupergirl,‚Äù DC Studios‚Äô newest feature film to hit the big screen, will be in theaters worldwide this summer from Warner Bros. Pictures, starring Milly Alcock in the dual role of Supergirl/Kara Zor-El.  Craig Gillespie directs the film from a screenplay by Ana Nogueira.

When an unexpected and ruthless adversary strikes too close to home, Kara Zor-El, aka Supergirl, reluctantly joins forces with an unlikely companion on an epic, interstellar journey of vengeance and justice.

Alcock stars alongside Matthias Schoenaerts, Eve Ridley, David Krumholtz, Emily Beecham, and Jason Momoa.

DC Studios heads Peter Safran and James Gunn are producing the film, which is based on characters from DC, Supergirl based on characters created by Jerry Siegel and Joe Shuster.  The film is executive produced by Nigel Gostelow, Chantal Nong Vo and Lars P. Winther.  Behind the camera, Gillespie is joined by director of photography Rob Hardy, production designer Neil Lamont, editor Tatiana S. Riegel, costume designer Anna B. Sheppard, Visual Effects Supervisor Geoffrey Baumann, and composer Ramin Djawadi.  

DC Studios Presents a Troll Court Entertainment Production, The Safran Company Production, A Film by Craig Gillespie, ‚ÄúSupergirl,‚Äù which will be in theaters and IMAX¬Æ across North America on June 26, 2026, and internationally beginning 24 June 2026, distributed by Warner Bros. Pictures.

localized.title: Supergirl | Official Teaser Trailer
localized.description:
Look out. #Supergirl lands in theaters June 26.

‚ÄúSupergirl,‚Äù DC Studios‚Äô newest feature film to hit the big screen, will be in theaters worldwide this summer from Warner Bros. Pictures, starring Milly Alcock in the dual role of Supergirl/Kara Zor-El.  Craig Gillespie directs the film from a screenplay by Ana Nogueira.

When an unexpected and ruthless adversary strikes too close to home, Kara Zor-El, aka Supergirl, reluctantly joins forces with an unlikely companion on an epic, interstellar journey of vengeance and justice.

Alcock stars alongside Matthias Schoenaerts, Eve Ridley, David Krumholtz, Emily Beecham, and Jason Momoa.

DC Studios heads Peter Safran and James Gunn are producing the film, which is based on characters from DC, Supergirl based on characters created by Jerry Siegel and Joe Shuster.  The film is executive produced by Nigel Gostelow, Chantal Nong Vo and Lars P. Winther.  Behind the camera, Gillespie is joined by director of photography Rob Hardy, production designer Neil Lamont, editor Tatiana S. Riegel, costume designer Anna B. Sheppard, Visual Effects Supervisor Geoffrey Baumann, and composer Ramin Djawadi.  

DC Studios Presents a Troll Court Entertainment Production, The Safran Company Production, A Film by Craig Gillespie, ‚ÄúSupergirl,‚Äù which will be in theaters and IMAX¬Æ across North America on June 26, 2026, and internationally beginning 24 June 2026, distributed by Warner Bros. Pictures.

#winterSong #newharyanvisong #newharyanvisongsharyanavi2025 #newharyanvisong2025 #hariyanvisong #haryanvi #haryanvisongs

Specail Thanks - Ankur Makdoli ,Yogesh Verma ,Bhanu Natwal ,Ravi Kharkiya, jaizeey Music Mackey Muzic , Diler ka Diwana ( Aashish )  , Sonu Malik , 



Lyrics : 

Aaj happy happy laage se
Makha jo kuch se tere aage se 

Aaj happy happy laage se
Makha jo kuch se tere aage se 

Aaj badli badli dikhe se , teri kyaki tyari ho rii se
In jhadya ohoooo
In jhadya mai jaan meri 
Mere byah ki tyari ho rii se

Yo ke matter se smjha na mai
Kr rakhya confuse tne 
Sabte pehla tere aage share krii good news mne 

Rr ghrkya nai tohh rakhya se 
Ya aape kr liya choose tne 
Meri pasand ka se chhora 
Woh rakhega mahfooz mne 

Haye meri pasand ka se chhora woh rakhega mahfooz mne 

Tu paapan dil ki kali mere te 
Kadd ki baat lakko rii se
Ho in jhadya mein ohoo

Ho in jhadya mein jaan meri mere byah ki tyari ho rii se - 3

Rr kit ka se husband tera na bera pta thikaane ka 
Sahar Bhiwani suna to hoga khas jhila hariyane ka

Rr kisne chhora tohya se tu naam bta us syaane ka
Tu jaane mhare bichole ne woh babaji nindhane ka 
Haaye jaane mhare bichole ne woh babaji nindhane ka 

Diler Kharkiya bandhra mera jis gail chle love story se
Oh in jhadya mein ohoo 
Oh in jhadya mein jaan meri mere byah ki tyari ho rii se - 2

snippet.title: Anuv Jain - INAAM (Official Music Video)
snippet.description:
Stream Inaam : https://UMGI.lnk.to/Inaam_AnuvJain

Audio Credits: 

Artist: Anuv Jain (@anuvjain)
Composer: Anuv Jain (@anuvjain)
Producer: Lost Stories (@loststories)
Acoustic, Electric and Bass Guitars: Keba Jeremiah (@kebajr)
Choirs: Solomon Konwar (@solomonkonwar) Prachi Kapil (@prachi.kapil8)
Mix Engineers: Rishab Joshi (@rishabjoshi) & Mukul Jain (@mixbymukul)
Master Engineer: Mukul Jain (@mixbymukul)
Additional Programming: Sarthak Kalyani (@sarthak.kalyani)
Dolby Atmos Mastered at Ferris Wheel Studios (@ferriswheelstudios)

Video Credits: 

Director: Bhagyesh Rajeshirke (@bhagyesh_rajeshirke)
Associate Director: Manthan Sharma (@manthan.mp4)
Creative Director: Pranjal Asha (@pranjalasha)
Editor: Manthan Sharma (@manthan.mp4)
Producer: Arnab Kar (@arnab_kar)

Management: REPRESENT
Managers: Shirsodhi Banerjee (@shirsodhi), Kartik Iyer (@kartik_iyer_)

Inaam Lyrics: 

Paragraph 1

Malum 
Hai na 
Hum janay 
Tumko tumse zyada

Tumko 
Mila hai woh
Saalon se 
Jo bhi hai manga

Pre-chorus 1

Kaise khilono ki 
Ro ro ke
Karte the mangay 

Ik bar mil jaye 
Do din mein
Hi bhul jatay  

Chorus 1

Lekin khilono ke dil 
Toh hote hi nahin the

Dil toh humara hai 
Janay galat kya sahi yeh

Kitna the chahte par
Ab tumko yaad na aatey 
Hum

Paragraph 2

Kya yaad tumko 
Tum humko
‚ÄòInaam‚Äô the kehte 

Karte the kitna kuch
Panay ki chah 
Mein pehlay 


Pre-chorus 2

Ab yeh inaam ka 
Tum pe ilzaam hai jana

Dil hai gawah
Jeete jabse ho
Tumko hai hara 

Chorus 2

Cheezein badalti hain 
Itna toh hum ne bhi mana

Itna badal jaogay 
Jana kisne tha jana  

Jo tha parvana 
Ab usko humari parwah na 
Kyun?

Pre-Bridge

Dil mein baat kya hai?
Haan bolo humse 

Chahta aur kya hai? 
Haan bolo humse

Kya kami yahan hai?
Haan bolo humse na

Jo kaha mila hai
Haan bolo humse 

Badle mein bhala hai
Haan bolo humse

Manga tumse kya hai
Hai manga zara sa hi, kya hi, 

Kya? haye

Bas 

Bridge

Jo khat likhe the tumne 
Unhe padh bhi lo zara 
Waadein kiye the jo bhi
Nibhao na aise kabhi

In waadon ki siyahi 
Abhi sukhi hi kahan?
Hai tumhari hi likhai
Yaan bhule ho ye bhi?

Paragraph 3

Kehne ko 
Wah wah 
Tum phir se 
Inaam ho jeete 

Chehre par
Muskan 
Par ankhein hain
Khush na kahin se 

Pre-chorus 3

Humne kaha tha
Hum janey tumko 
Tumse zyada 

Shayad galat the 
Par itna toh 
Humne hai jana 

Chorus 3

Har woh inaam 
Qadar ke bina hi hai waise 

Ghar mein padhe, 
Dhul khate khilono ke jaise

Pal bhar behlaye 
Par dil ko yeh khush na kar paye 
Yoon

Hidden verse

Ghar bethe likhta tha 
Dil ki kahani meri 

Charon taraf thi deewarein 
Deewaron se hi 

Kehta tha ik din 
Jahaan hoga haathon mein hi

Aa aa

Jo tha gumnamo mein 
Ab woh inaamon pe bhi 

Qaidi hai, Qaid hi hai 
Phir bhi dewaron mein hi 

Namumkin khwabon mein
Na khush udane meri 

Aa aa

snippet.description:
üî• The BR Main Event BEGINS! Day 1 is HERE! üî•

After an intense Play-Ins stage, the top teams have finally arrived at the Main Event of the Free Fire MAX Asia Invitational 2025!

This is where the real battle begins ‚Äî the stage where champions rise and every point matters.

The leaderboard starts fresh today. Only the most consistent, most fearless, and most strategic squads will survive across the Main Event battle days. Every fight is a statement. Every drop could decide the throne.

Today, Group B takes on Group C to open the Main Event in high voltage fashion.

Playing Today:
Group B: REVENANT XSPARK, NIGHTMARE ESPORTS, IQOO TOTAL GAMING ESPORTS, GOW ESPORTS, KAGENDRA, RED HAWKS.
Group C: META NINZA, S8ULELITE, P ESPORTS, BIGETRON BY VITALITY, MAQNA ESPORTS CLUB, DRS GAMING.

The energy is high, the fans are loud, and the journey to crown the FFMAI 2025 champions officially begins today.

12 Teams. 1 Massive Opening Fight. The Main Event starts NOW! üëë

Cricket Live




Mullanpur is set to host its maiden men's international cricket match, and the setting couldn't be more perfect. There's the December chill in the air, the finalists of the last T20 World Cup are facing off, and yet what's to be expected from Punjab's latest international venue is as unclear as Chandigarh's air itself, hazy with smog.

India vs South Africa 2nd T20 Match, Aaj Ki Raat, 7 bajy se

When: Thursday, December 11, 2025, 7:00 PM IST

Where: Maharaja Yadavindra Singh International Cricket Stadium, Mullanpur, New Chandigarh

What to expect: Some fog, some dew, and some advantage to the chasing team - even as four of the six IPL matches played at the venue was won by the team batting first.

Team News

India: There are no reported injuries, and there would be a scope to experiment with their options.

Probable XI: Abhishek Sharma, Shubman Gill, Suryakumar Yadav, Tilak Varma, Hardik Pandya, Shivam Dube, Jitesh Sharma, Axar Patel, Arshdeep Singh, Kuldeep Yadav, Jasprit Bumrah

South Africa: The visitors might look to retain their combination, allowing them more time to get accustomed to the conditions

Probable XI: Quinton de Kock, Aiden Markram, Tristan Stubbs, Dewald Brevis, David Miller, Donovan Ferreira, Marco Jansen, Corbin Bosch, Keshav Maharaj, Anrich Nortje, Lungi Ngidi



After winning the ODI Series Against South Africa by 2-1, Now Blue shirts have to play 5 T20 Match series against the guest.

India vs South Africa Highlights Today
India have to play almost 10 T20i Matches before the ICC Men's T20 Cricket World Cup 2026. This is an opportunity to maintain momentum & chose the best 11 players for upcoming event. After the 3 match ODI Series, India will play 5 T20 Match Matches against South Africa at home. Afterwards, New Zealand cricket team will visit India.

Here is the teams list that will participate in the next T20 World Cup 2026.

T20 World Cup 2026 teams and groups
Group A: India, Pakistan, Netherlands, Namibia, USA.
Group B: Sri Lanka, Australia, Zimbabwe, Ireland, Oman.
Group C: England, West Indies, Bangladesh, Nepal. Italy.
Group D: South Africa, New Zealand, Afghanistan, UAE, Canada. India vs Pakistan T20 Cricket World Cup Match Will be played on February 15 2026.

Designed with a cinematic narrative approach, the project showcases the evolving identity of Khandeshi music through world-class production techniques, precise visual storytelling, and polished sound design.

This film-style music video reflects a new direction in regional artistry, elevating local culture with an international visual and audio standard.
